{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/2017-09-28--Using-bluetooth-on-kali-linux/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Joel's dev blog","author":"Joel Mun","siteUrl":"https://9oelm.github.io"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"e2cdbd31-75e5-55d2-8036-e652a79650ee","excerpt":"Check bluetooth status And turn it on: This way bluetooth is going to work.   will stop bluetooth. Bluetooth is not turned on by default on boot on kali linuxâ€¦","html":"<p>Check bluetooth status</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">/etc/init.d/bluetooth status</code></pre></div>\n<p>And turn it on:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">/etc/init.d/bluetooth start</code></pre></div>\n<p>This way bluetooth is going to work. </p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">stop</code> will stop bluetooth.</p>\n<p>Bluetooth is not turned on by default on boot on kali linux.</p>\n<p>Another equivalent way is:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">service bluetooth start(stop)</code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">service bluetooth status</code></pre></div>","frontmatter":{"title":"Using bluetooth on kali linux","date":"September 28, 2017"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/2017-09-28--Using-bluetooth-on-kali-linux/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/2017-09-28--Using-vim/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Using vim"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/2017-09-29--Using-tor/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Using tor"}}}},"staticQueryHashes":["3128451518","426816048"]}